{{Reflist|group="note"|30em|refs=
<ref group="note" name="IEDOM2">Internet Explorer 5 and above has [http://www.quirksmode.org/js/events_advanced.html its own event registration model] and [http://www.quirksmode.org/dom/changess.html its own style sheets model], but these are incompatible with DOM 2.</ref>
<ref group="note" name="MozXPath">XPath is a part of DOM 3, but is considered separately here. A large subset of DOM 3 is accessible by extensions but not by websites.</ref>
<ref group="note" name="SafariNightly">SVG / XPath / (partial) DOM 3 is only available in the WebKit nightlies so far.</ref>
<ref group="note" name="AmayaScript">It is possible to compile [https://web.archive.org/web/20071225120656/http://www.maths-informatique-jeux.com/international/javascript_in_amaya/ Amaya with JavaScript enabled], using the CVS version and [[SpiderMonkey (JavaScript engine)|SpiderMonkey]]. However, this is still experimental and only a small subset of DOM 1 is available.</ref>
<ref group="note" name="LinksScript">Support for JavaScript has been removed in version 2.1pre29 ([http://links.twibright.com/download/ChangeLog change log])</ref>
}}

