{{Reflist|group="note"|30em|refs=
<ref group="note" name="External2">Many browsers have FTP support as read-only and have no upload capitilies. Read-only is marked as yes. For a comparison of clients that support upload opportunities see [[Comparison of FTP client software]].</ref>
<ref group="note" name="External3">Many browsers have purposely avoided support for e-mail and newsgroups ([[Usenet]]), as these are reserved for their mail-client counterparts. For a comparison of such counterparts see [[comparison of e-mail clients]] and [[Comparison of Usenet newsreaders]].</ref>
<!--IE is declared above because of nested tags-->
<ref group="note" name="Mosaic">Mosaic reached only HTTP 0.9 compliance, and does not support secure communications in any way.</ref>
<ref group="note" name="ChatZilla">IRC support can be added by installing [[ChatZilla]].</ref>
<ref group="note" name="FirefoxGopherDropped">Firefox support for the Gopher protocol was dropped in Firefox 4 (Gecko 1.9.3) per [https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=388195 bug 388195]. This and newer versions have full Gopher support when the OverbiteFF extension is installed.</ref>
<ref group="note" name="OpGopher">Includes a proxy capability for gopher support.</ref>
<ref group="note" name="IEGopher">Internet Explorer 7 has no support of gopher; gopher support is disabled in IE6</ref>
<ref group="note" name="MozIDN">For security reasons, IDN domains are displayed as [[punycode]] if they contain certain characters or if the [[top level domain]] has not been [[whitelist]]ed [http://kb.mozillazine.org/Network.IDN.blacklist_chars].</ref>
<ref group="note" name="KonqGopher">Konqueror has full Gopher support when the kgopher KIO plugin is installed.</ref>
<ref group="note" name="NNTP">[[NNTP]] support can be added by installing the add-on [[infoRSS]].</ref>
<ref group="note" name="DilloSSL">Dillo has experimental SSL integration that is by standard turned off. {{cite web |url=http://www.dillo.org/FAQ.html#q12 |title=How do I enable the https (SSL) support plugin for dillo? |accessdate=12 April 2017|postscript=.}} There is no certificate caching and ''no authentication'' performed.</ref>
<ref group="note" name="firetorrent">Possible using third party extensions like [https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/foxtorrent/?src=search FoxTorrent]</ref>
<ref group="note" name="no-ui">Behavior towards malicious certificates can only be set up in [[compiler|compile time]].</ref>
<!--IEdataprotocol is declared above because of nested ref tags-->
}}

