'''Paigham-i-Pakistan''' or ''' Paigham-e-Pakistan''' ({{lang-en|Message of Pakistan|italics=yes}} {{lang-ur|{{URDU|پیغام پاکستان}}}}) is a [[fatwa]] sought by the [[Government of Pakistan]] to counter [[Terrorism in Pakistan|terrorism]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1383306/govt-unveils-paigham-i-pakistan-fatwa-against-terrorism |title=Govt unveils 'Paigham-i-Pakistan' fatwa against terrorism |last=Dawn.com |date=2018-01-16 |work=DAWN.COM |access-date=2018-01-16 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.bbc.com/urdu/pakistan-42702303 |title=’پیغام پاکستان‘: انتہا پسندی کے خلاف نیا بیانیہ |last=رشید |first=ہارون |date=2018 |work=BBC News Urdu |access-date=2018-01-16 |language=en-GB}}</ref> The fatwa was prepared by [[International Islamic University, Islamabad|International Islamic University]] and signed by 1,800 scholars from various [[Madhhab|Islamic schools of thought]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1610044/1-1800-pakistani-religious-scholars-declare-suicide-bombings-haram-new-fatwa/ |title=1,800 Pakistani religious scholars declare suicide bombings 'haram' in new fatwa - The Express Tribune |date=2018-01-16 |work=The Express Tribune |access-date=2018-01-16 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thequint.com/news/world/pak-issues-paigham-e-pakistan-fatwa-against-1800-extremist-scholars |title=Pak Issues ‘Paigham-e-Pakistan’ Fatwa Against 1,800 Extremists |work=The Quint |access-date=2018-01-17 |language=en}}</ref>
