{{Multiple issues| {{POV|date=April 2015}}{{notability|Web|date=April 2015}} {{Underlinked|date=March 2018}} }}
'''ProgrammableWeb''' is an information and news source about the Web as a programmable platform. It is a subsidiary of [[MuleSoft]] and has offices in San Francisco, CA. The website publishes a repository of web APIs, mashups, and applications, and has documented over 12,000 open web [[Application programming interface|APIs]] and thousands of applications.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.programmableweb.com/apis/directory|title=API Directory|work=ProgrammableWeb}}</ref> It has been called the "journal of the API economy" by TechCrunch.<ref name = "editor">{{cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2013/08/07/veteran-news-editor-david-berlind-joins-programmable-web-the-journal-of-the-api-economy/|title=Veteran News Editor David Berlind Joins Programmable Web, The Journal Of The API Economy|publisher=AOL|work=TechCrunch}}</ref>
== History == ProgrammableWeb was founded in 2005 by John Musser and had documented 1,000 APIs by November 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2008/11/03/let-a-thousand-web-apis-blossom/|title=Let A Thousand Web APIs Blossom|publisher=AOL|work=TechCrunch}}</ref>
In June 2010, Alcatel-Lucent acquired ProgrammableWeb as part of a move by the company to align themselves closer to the developer community.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/alcatel-lucent-acquires-leading-web-20-api-repository-programmableweb-97374309.html|title=Alcatel-Lucent Acquires Leading Web 2.0 API Repository ProgrammableWeb|author=Alcatel-Lucent|date=29 June 2010|work=prnewswire.com}}</ref> Alcatel-Lucent was looking to integrate ProgrammableWeb’s API monitoring services and other API related technologies with its own Open API Service and Developer Platform to strengthen its relationship with developers. During ProgrammableWeb’s time with Alcatel-Lucent, they documented over 8,000 APIs.
Three years later on April 13, 2013, MuleSoft announced the acquisition of ProgrammableWeb to "become the go-to destination for APIs and Integration”.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mulesoft.com/mulesoft-acquires-programmableweb|title=MuleSoft Acquires ProgrammableWeb|work=MuleSoft}}</ref><ref> {{cite web |url= https://thenextweb.com/insider/2013/04/23/programmableweb-the-destination-for-all-things-api-gets-acquired-again-this-time-by-mulesoft/#.tnw_LkcmKVNQ |title= ProgrammableWeb – the destination for all things API – gets bought again, this time by MuleSoft |first= Robin |last= Wauters|date= 23 April 2013|publisher= The Next Web |accessdate= 26 May 2017 }} </ref>
== Content == ProgrammableWeb.com has two major sections:
* '''API Directory and Technology Listings:''' A massive searchable directory of over 15,500 web APIs that are updated daily<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.programmableweb.com/about|title=About ProgrammableWeb|work=ProgrammableWeb}}</ref> as well as listings of various mashups, applications, frameworks, libraries, and SDKs. * '''News, Analysis, and Reviews:''' Daily news on web technology, APIs, and other relevant web information as well as analysis of current trends and reviews of various web technologies.
== References == {{reflist}}
