The '''Rangjung Yeshe Wiki''' is a Wiki community established in 2005 focussing on building a Tibetan-English Dictionary, glossaries of Buddhist terminology, biographies of Buddhist teachers, data on important Tibetan Buddhist literary works and collections, and developing resources useful for the "community of [[lotsawa]]s" involved in translating Buddhist texts from Classical Tibetan to English and other European Languages.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rywiki.tsadra.org/index.php/Main_Page|title=Rangjung Yeshe Wiki - Dharma Dictionary:Main Page |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |website=Rangjung Yeshe Wiki |publisher=Tsadra Foundation |accessdate=24 November 2013}}</ref> The original content of the Wiki was based on a digital Tibetan-English dictionary compiled by the translator [[Erik Pema Kunsang]] since the early 1970s. The Rangjung Yeshe Wiki currently has over 23,720 content pages, 1,060 uploaded files, and 825 registered users.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rywiki.tsadra.org/index.php/Special:Statistics|title=Statistics - Rangjung Yeshe Wiki - Dharma Dictionary |publisher=Tsadra Foundation |accessdate=2013-11-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wikiapiary.com/wiki/Rangjung_Yeshe_Wiki_-_Dharma_Dictionnary|title=Rangjung Yeshe Wiki - Dharma Dictionary |website=WikiApiary |accessdate=2013-11-23}}</ref> The site is hosted and supported by the [[Tsadra Foundation]].
