{{Infobox scientist |name = Robert P. Higgins |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = 1932 |birth_place = United States |death_date = |residence = |citizenship = |nationality = American |ethnicity = |field = [[Natural history]] |work_institutions = [[National Museum of Natural History]] [[Smithsonian Institution]] |alma_mater = |known_for = |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = |influenced = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = |signature = }}
'''Robert P. Higgins''' (born 1932) is a systematic [[Invertebrate zoology|invertebrate zoologist]] and [[ecologist]]. He worked as a researcher at the [[Smithsonian Institution]], where he began in 1968 as an [[Oceanography|oceanographer]]. Higgins served as Director of the Centre for Mediterranean Marine Classification 1969-1971, Program Director of [[Limnology]] and Oceanography, 1971-1974, Acting Director, International Programme on Environmental Sciences in 1974, [[Zoologist]] Superior from 1974 to 1978, and Curator, Department of Invertebrate Zoology, [[National Museum of Natural History]] in 1978. Higgins retired in 1996.
== Publications == '''Incomplete''' * 1975: Occurrence of the genus Tanarctus Renaud-Debyser, 1959 in Northeastern Atlantic waters with a description of T. ramazzotti n. sp. (Arthrotardigrada).<ref>Renaud-Mornant, J. and Higgins, R.P., eds., 1975. Occurrence of the genus Tanarctus Renaud-Debyser, 1959 in Northeastern Atlantic waters with a description of T. ramazzotti n. sp. (Arthrotardigrada). Memorie dell'Istituto Italiano di Idrobiologia Dott. Marco de Marchi, vol. 32, suppl.: International Symposium on Tardigrades, Pallanza, Italy, June 17–19, 1974: 325-332.</ref> * 1983: The atlantic barrier reef ecosistema at Carrie Bow cay, Belize, II: Kinorhyncha.<ref>Higgins, Robert R.P. 1983: The atlantic barrier reef ecosistema at Carrie Bow cay, Belize, II: Kinorhyncha.Smithsonian Contribution to the Marine Sciences, 18 131p.</ref> * 1984: A New Family of Arthrotardigrada (Tardigrada: Heterotardigrada) from the Atlantic Coast of Florida, U.S.A.<ref>[[Reinhardt Kristensen|Kristensen, R.M.]] and Higgins, R.P., 1984. A New Family of Arthrotardigrada (Tardigrada: Heterotardigrada) from the Atlantic Coast of Florida, U.S.A. Transactions of the American Microscopical Society, vol. 103, no. 3: 295-311.</ref> * 1986: New Loricifera from southeastern United States coastal Waters.<ref>Higgins, Robert P.; [[Reinhardt Kristensen|Kristensen, R.M.]]. 1986: New Loricifera from southeastern United States coastal waters Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 438 Smithsonian Institution Press: Washington D.C.. III, 70 pp. ISSN 0081-0282</ref> * 1988: Introduction to the Study of Meiofauna.<ref>Higgins, R.P. and Thiel, Hjalmar. 1988: Introduction to the Study of Meiofauna. Smithsonian Institution Press, 1988 – 488</ref>
