{{Infobox book | name = What's Your Poo Telling You? | image = WhatsYorPoTellingYou-Book.jpg | caption = | author = [[Josh Richman (writer)|Josh Richman]] and [[Anish Sheth]], MD | illustrator = [[Peter Arkle]] | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = | genre = [[humor]] and [[medical]] | publisher = [[Chronicle Books]] | release_date = June 2007 | english_release_date = | media_type = Print (Hardcover) | pages = 96 pp (first edition, hardcover) | isbn = 0-8118-5782-4 | isbn_note = (first edition, hardcover) | dewey= 612.3/6 22 | congress= QP159 .R53 2007 | oclc= 829960587 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''What's Your Poo Telling You?''''' is a book for adults describing different aspects of human [[flatulence]], [[defecation]], [[diarrhea]], and various [[feces]]-related phenomena.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Goldman|first1=Leslie|title=Good Literature Bathroom humor with a serious side|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2007-06-10/features/0706060495_1_poor-taste-high-fiber-content-stool|publisher=Chicago Tribune|accessdate=7 October 2015}}</ref> The book sold well upon its release and in 2009 the book was reported to have sold over 400,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stannard|first1=Ed|title=Much to be learned in restroom, author says|url=http://www.nhregister.com/general-news/20091117/much-to-be-learned-in-restroom-author-says|publisher=New Haven Register|accessdate=7 October 2015}}</ref>
It was authored by [[Josh Richman (writer)|Josh Richman]] and [[gastroenterologist]] Anish Sheth, M.D.<ref>{{Cite web|title = You Asked: What Is My Poo Telling Me?|url = http://time.com/3625206/poop-health/|website = TIME.com|accessdate = 2015-10-06|first = Markham|last = Heid}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Look Inside the Toilet Bowl to Learn About Your Health|url = http://www.womenshealthmag.com/health/fix-stomach-problems|accessdate = 2015-10-06}}</ref> It includes diagrams provided by illustrator Peter Arkle. The book was followed up by two companion pieces, ''What's My Pee Telling Me?'' (2009) and ''What's Your Baby's Poo Telling You?'' (2014).<ref>{{cite web|title=Un libro enseña a los padres a "leer" el pañal de sus hijos|url=http://www.elpais.com.uy/vida-actual/libro-ensena-padres-leer-panal.html|publisher=El Pais|accessdate=7 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Hicks|first1=Lily|title=Potty talk "What’s My Pee Telling Me?"|url=http://dailycollegian.com/2010/03/21/potty-talk-whats-my-pee-telling-me/|publisher=Daily Collegian|accessdate=7 October 2015}}</ref> Merchandise tie-ins for the series include a daily calendar, log, mobile app, and an activity book.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Armstrong Moore|first1=Elizabeth|title=Great, now Apple is invading my intestines|url=http://www.cnet.com/news/great-now-apple-is-invading-my-intestines/#!|publisher=CNET|accessdate=7 October 2015}}</ref>
